<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36208j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36208j">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36208j"> 208(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Willing Workers / Busy Bees</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Atheism.]</font> And suppose we look at the names which the various branches over the country have given themselves. Is there a vast difference between the &ldquo;<mark>Busy Bees</mark>&rdquo; of The Presbyterian Sunday School at Kaufman, Texas, and the &ldquo;Devil&apos;s Angels&rdquo; of Los Angeles? &hellip; When a Sunday School calls itself the &ldquo;<mark>Willing Workers</mark>,&rdquo; it accepts a banner, a religious ideal, and it intends to fit itself into a tradition. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 434</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
